    {
      "index": 0,
      "text": "India versus Pakistan. Technology and internet race. Who wins?",
      "startFrame": 0,
      "endFrame": 152
    },
    {
      "index": 1,
      "text": "Start with internet users. India has hundreds of millions more people online.",
      "startFrame": 164,
      "endFrame": 306
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "text": "Smartphone penetration and total app market size also heavily favor India.",
      "startFrame": 318,
      "endFrame": 459
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "text": "IT exports are where the difference becomes dramatic. India is a global giant. Pakistan is still far smaller.",
      "startFrame": 471,
      "endFrame": 675
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "text": "Startup scale and venture funding also point strongly toward India.",
      "startFrame": 687,
      "endFrame": 813
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "text": "Digital payments are another major advantage. India built one of the biggest instant payment systems on Earth.",
      "startFrame": 825,
      "endFrame": 1013
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "text": "Pakistan is growing fast online, but it is still playing catch-up in size and capital.",
      "startFrame": 1025,
      "endFrame": 1189
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "text": "So if the contest is modern tech scale, India wins clearly.",
